{
  "type": "elizaosDailySummary",
  "title": "Daily Report - 2026-04-24",
  "categories": [
    {
      "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion - April 24, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "A developer from Elisym Labs shared a demo of the plugin-elizaos-elisym plugin, which was recently merged into the ElizaOS plugin registry. The plugin turns any Eliza agent into a paid provider by publishing capabilities to a Nostr-based discovery layer and earning SOL when other agents call them. The demo showed an agent announcing itself on Nostr, receiving a paid request from Claude desktop for trending GitHub repos, and settling payment on Solana devnet. The full agent-to-agent flow involves discovery on Nostr and settlement on Solana with no intermediary platform.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/plugin-elizaos-elisym_f71dc814.jpg",
          "videos": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/2047445235488182370_8203d0bc.mp4"
        },
        {
          "text": "Community members discussed potential utility for the ELIZAOS token. One user proposed that a future version of the protocol could allow users to pay protocol fees in either USDC or ELIZAOS, with a discount for paying in the native token and a backend buyback and burn mechanism for USDC payments, drawing a comparison to the early BNB model. This suggestion motivated core developer Odilitime to resume work from November on a feature for the 1.x branch that would allow plugins to accept ELIZAOS and DegenAI as x402 payments, describing it as the lowest hanging fruit for token utility. Odilitime also mentioned speaking with Shaw and planned to update working groups.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1777079946713-7n4m7.png"
        },
        {
          "text": "A community member shared an image suggesting an app icon concept for ElizaOS, prompting a reply that the design should be simplified and use a maximum of three colors. Separately, a scam message was flagged by multiple users in the channel. Odilitime also conducted a cozy devs role check by tagging several core developers, and a senior developer introduced themselves in the channel, offering services in AI, voice AI, web and mobile development, and cloud infrastructure, and was directed to post in the appropriate hiring channel.",
          "sources": "https://discord.com/channels/1253563208833433701/1253563209462448241",
          "images": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/elizaos-media/embed-image-1497057655175516160_91e1adfc.jpg"
        }
      ],
      "topic": "discordrawdata"
    },
    {
      "title": "Overall Project Summary - April 24, 2026",
      "content": {
        "text": "On April 24, 2026, the ElizaOS team concentrated on stabilizing core infrastructure and expanding agent capabilities across several fronts. A major milestone was the completion of the LifeOps multi-calendar stack, which now supports listing, persistence, and merging of multiple Google Calendar feeds with hosted cloud latency fallbacks. Action correction logic was also refined to ensure SPAWN_AGENT actions are properly preserved during metadata corrections. On the frontend side, excessive polling was reduced across the MusicPlayer, ChatView, and ConversationsSidebar components to improve resource efficiency. An OAuth authentication failure in the Steward flow was resolved by correcting the tenant_id parameter format. CI/CD work included stabilizing the plugin-anthropic pipeline for standalone publishing and fixing malformed Haiku model IDs that had been causing API 404 errors. A broad set of dependency updates was also applied across the framework, covering packages such as @elizaos/core, telegram, vite, and vitest. A previously open issue requesting trustless agent-to-agent deals via local ZK proofs was closed. Numerous additional pull requests are currently in progress across the main elizaos/eliza repository.",
        "sources": "https://elizaos.github.io/api/summaries/overall/day/2026-04-24.json",
        "posters": "https://cdn.elizaos.news/posters/1777079977712-4scu3j.png"
      },
      "topic": "miscellaneous"
    }
  ],
